Linux-Apps

# how make a script exec on startUP

 
	1. Create Your Bash Script:
	2. Create a systemd Service File:

	   Create a file with a `.service` extension, in the `/etc/systemd/system/` directory.
	   
	   	>> sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/myscript.service
	  

	3. Edit the `.service` File:

	   Add the following content to the `myscript.service` file:

	    [Unit]
		Description=Run checkin_scrape.py before shutdown

		[Service]
		Type=oneshot
		ExecStart=python3 /home/sandeep-vassar/Documents/scripts/checkInScape/checkin_scrape.py
		ExecStop=python3 /home/sandeep-vassar/Documents/scripts/checkInScape/checkin_scrape.py

		[Install]
		WantedBy=multi-user.target

	4. Reload systemd:

	   After creating the service file, reload the systemd manager to read the new service.
	   	>> sudo systemctl daemon-reload

	5. Enable the Service:

	   Enable the service to start at boot:
	   	 >> sudo systemctl enable myscript.service
	  
	6. Start the Service:

	   You can start the service immediately without rebooting:
	   >> sudo systemctl start myscript.service

	   	stop::
	   
	   >> sudo systemctl stop myscript.service
	   
	7. Check Status:

	   sudo systemctl status myscript.service